cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a deep neural network for person identification using gait under multiple views. This involves identifying spatio-temporal features and performing extensive experimentation and training mechanism. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training the network, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep neural networks also suggests the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper involves working with video data, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves biometric identification, which falls under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
